column3: Cheap, quick fried chicken joint as expected. Has counter service, limited seating; mostly take-out and delivery . Not Michelin 5 star, but does the job when a greasy meal is your craving: food is consistent and edible. They have your basic comfort foods (mashed potatoes, mac & cheese, french fries, onion rings, etc.). Also have dessert (pre-sliced cakes etc ) and pre-made salad bowls. Also several flavors of ice cream available at separate counter. Open late (till midnight,  or later, depending on the day). Very clean, professional and courteous staff. Have pandemic safety shields at counter. ADDED: they are no longer halal here.

column3: On th√© pricier side, but the dirty banana milk was so good. I‚Äôve never had a drink like this before. Unfortunately, they ran out of pearls ü•≤ ‚Ä¶

As a lifetime boba enthusiast, the Boba Guys have the best quality boba in the city. Since the rising popularity of bubble tea in general, most places have drinks that are powdery, too sweet, and can never get their boba right (they‚Äôre always undercooked, overcooked, or taste like absolutely nothing). I feel that overall we‚Äôve lost the authentic taste of bubble tea made with real tea leaves, quality ingredients, and the focus on perfecting the boba that was such a staple from my childhood. But anything and everything I get from Boba Guys exceeds my expectations and I can finally say I‚Äôve found boba that I truly enjoy again. Their classic drinks never miss, and their seasonal specials are always creative and delicious. Anyone who asks me where to go for bubble I always direct them here, even my family members who live on the west coast always make Boba Guys a necessary stop in their trips here. I‚Äôm a little sad they have less locations now but I don‚Äôt mind commuting for this. Hopefully we can see some more open soon and maybe even in queens!

column3: Came here and got the pandan caramel matcha with almond jelly! I was pleasantly surprised with the caramel - I thought it would be too sweet but it was a really nice touch. I think the pandan flavor was not very strong and the matcha was pretty overpowering. I thought it was still good but if you wanted a strong pandan flavor you might be disappointed.

I used to live in the Bay and was sad to find no Boba Guys in NYC. Now that they‚Äôre here, I‚Äôm reminded how great they are. One of the best bubble tea spots in the area.  The bubbles are the perfect QQ texture and their menu is eclectic but still simple ranging from traditional black milk tea to options like strawberry matcha or horchata.  I highly recommend  The shop itself is very small and standing-room only. They sell a small selection of merch in addition to their drinks.

column3: Amazingly efficient restaurant. There's a line but a lady with a tablet allows you to order while waiting in line. When you reach the cash register you just have to mention your name and after payment you immediately get your order as it already has been prepared. Quite some seating upstairs. For free drink refills you have to go back to the counter downstairs unfortunately. Restroom is at the upper floor. Restroom door code is at the bottom of the receipt. Restroom was clean but there's only one. There's a staff member dedicated to keeping the seating area clean. Free WiFi available. Excellent tasting food. Free sauces.
